b'' b'scott evans <server.cs.virginia.edu writes:' b" i'm trying to create a button that has both a label and a bitmap using" b' the menubutton widget. is this possible? right now, all i get is the' b' bitmap no sign of the label.' b'' b"that's expected. the first sentence describing the bitmap resource in the" b'menubutton section of the "athena widget set c language interface"' b'documentation states' b'' b'bitmap a bitmap to display instead of the label.' b'' b"one way round this might be to make use of the button's backgroundpixmap" b"resource, but remember that you, or a user of your application, won't be able" b"to set it from a resource file. also, the button won't automatically be the" b'size of the bitmap. the bitmap will be tiled if necessary, or you could set the' b"button's dimensions to match its size." b'' b'jim' b'---' b'department of computing science, university of newcastle, tel: b'newcastle upon tyne, ne1 7ru, united kingdom. fax: b'' b'' 